(44, 13, 36, 13, 18, 14, 14, 'served his own generation by the will of God', 'David''s Leadership and Legacy', 'Both passages emphasize David''s role in serving his generation and executing justice. Acts highlights his service by the will of God, while Chronicles reflects his reign and judgment over Israel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 36, 1, 3, 19, 19, 'saw corruption', 'Connection of Mortality and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the inevitability of death. Acts 13:36 mentions David''s death and corruption, while Genesis 3:19 speaks of returning to dust, highlighting the human condition of mortality.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 36, 13, 13, 2, 4, 'served his own generation by the will of God', 'David''s Leadership and Service', 'This connection highlights David''s role in serving his generation and leading Israel to seek the ark of God. Both passages emphasize David''s commitment to fulfilling God''s will among his people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 37, 44, 13, 30, 30, 'God raised again', 'Resurrection of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize God''s action in raising Jesus from the dead. Acts 13:30 states, ''But God raised him from the dead,'' while Acts 13:37 highlights that he ''saw no corruption'' after this resurrection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 37, 44, 2, 24, 24, 'saw no corruption', 'Resurrection and Corruption', 'Both passages emphasize God''s action in raising Jesus from the dead. Acts 13:37 states that Jesus ''saw no corruption,'' while Acts 2:24 highlights that death could not hold Him, indicating His victory over death.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 42, 24, 47, 47, 'forgiveness of sins', 'Forgiveness and Remission of Sins', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness and the preaching of remission of sins. Acts 13:38 speaks of forgiveness through Jesus, while Luke 24:47 mentions remission of sins to be preached in His name.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 47, 5, 18, 21, 'forgiveness of sins', 'Forgiveness and Reconciliation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of reconciliation and forgiveness through Jesus Christ. Acts 13:38 speaks of the ''forgiveness of sins,'' while 2 Corinthians 5:18-21 discusses God reconciling the world to Himself, not imputing trespasses. This connection highlights the transformative power of Christ''s sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 62, 2, 12, 12, 'forgiveness of sins', 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness of sins. Acts 13:38 states that forgiveness is preached through Jesus, while 1 John 2:12 affirms that sins are forgiven for His name''s sake.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 44, 5, 31, 31, 'forgiveness of sins', 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness of sins through Jesus. Acts 13:38 speaks of forgiveness being preached, while Acts 5:31 mentions forgiveness as a gift from God through Jesus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 51, 1, 14, 14, 'forgiveness of sins', 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the forgiveness of sins as a central theme. Acts 13:38 presents forgiveness through Jesus, while Colossians 1:14 highlights it through His blood.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 44, 2, 38, 38, NULL, 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness of sins. Acts 13:38 speaks of forgiveness through Jesus, while Acts 2:38 mentions remission of sins through repentance and baptism.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 38, 49, 1, 7, 7, 'forgiveness of sins', 'Forgiveness of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of forgiveness of sins through Christ. Acts 13:38 presents the preaching of forgiveness, while Ephesians 1:7 highlights redemption and forgiveness through his blood.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 45, 10, 4, 4, 'justified from all things', 'Justification and the Law', 'Both passages emphasize justification through faith rather than the law. Acts 13:39 states believers are justified from things the law cannot justify, while Romans 10:4 declares Christ as the end of the law for righteousness.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 48, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that justification comes through faith rather than the law. Acts 13:39 states believers are justified from all things, while Galatians 2:16 clarifies that no one is justified by the works of the law.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 45, 8, 3, 3, 'justified from all things', 'Justification and the Law', 'This connection highlights the inability of the law to justify believers, as noted in both passages. Acts 13:39 states that believers are justified from all things, while Romans 8:3 emphasizes what the law could not do due to its weakness.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 58, 7, 19, 19, 'justified from all things', 'Justification and Perfection in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of justification through faith in Christ as opposed to the law, which is seen as imperfect. Both passages emphasize that the law cannot achieve perfection or justification, pointing to a better hope found in Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 43, 1, 17, 17, 'justified from all things', 'Justification and Grace Contrast', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the law given by Moses and the grace that comes through Jesus Christ. Both passages emphasize that justification cannot be achieved through the law, but rather through faith in Christ.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 48, 3, 21, 25, 'justified from all things', 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize justification through faith rather than the law. Acts 13:39 states believers are justified from all things, while Galatians 3:24 highlights the law as a schoolmaster leading to justification by faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 39, 58, 10, 11, 11, 'justified from all things', 'Justification and Sacrifice Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between justification through faith and the ineffectiveness of the law and sacrifices. Acts 13:39 emphasizes justification from all things, while Hebrews 10:11 notes that sacrifices can never take away sins.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 39, 4, 1, 1, 'which is spoken of in the prophets', 'Judgment and Warning Connection', 'This connection highlights a warning of impending judgment. Both passages emphasize the consequences for the proud and wicked, with Acts referencing prophetic warnings and Malachi describing the destructive day of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 35, 1, 5, 5, 'that come upon you', 'Warning of Unbelief', 'This connection highlights a warning against disbelief in God''s work. Both passages emphasize the unexpected nature of God''s actions, urging the audience to be aware of the consequences of not believing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 39, 3, 2, 2, 'which is spoken of in the prophets', 'Judgment and Refinement Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and purification. Acts 13:40 warns of consequences foretold by the prophets, while Malachi 3:2 speaks of the refining process associated with the coming of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 58, 3, 12, 12, NULL, 'Warning Against Unbelief', 'This connection highlights the theme of caution against unbelief. Both passages emphasize the need to be vigilant to avoid departing from faith in God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 58, 12, 25, 25, 'that come upon you, which is spoken of in the prophets', 'Warning Against Rejection', 'This connection highlights the theme of warning against rejecting God''s message. Both passages emphasize the consequences of refusing to heed divine communication, whether from prophets or from heaven.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 40, 3, 9, 12, 'that come upon you, which is spoken of in the prophets', 'Warning of Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of impending judgment and the call for repentance. Both passages emphasize the consequences of failing to produce good fruit and the urgency of heeding prophetic warnings.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 40, 23, 29, 14, 14, 'which is spoken of in the prophets', 'Connection of Wisdom and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention leading to the downfall of human wisdom. Both passages emphasize the consequences of ignoring God''s message, as seen in the loss of understanding among the wise.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 41, 35, 1, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Works', 'Both passages emphasize a divine work that will occur in the listeners'' days, which they will not believe. The call to ''wonder'' and the warning against disbelief are central themes in both texts.', 'theme', 0.7549999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 41, 60, 4, 17, 17, 'ye shall in no wise believe', 'Judgment and Unbelief Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment beginning with those who have received the message, as seen in both passages. Acts 13:41 warns of disbelief leading to perishing, while 1 Peter 4:17 emphasizes judgment starting at the house of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 41, 45, 11, 7, 14, 'work which ye shall in no wise believe', 'Spiritual Blindness and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of spiritual blindness among Israel and the surprising work of God that leads to salvation for the Gentiles. Acts 13:41''s warning about disbelief resonates with Romans 11:7-8''s depiction of Israel being blinded, highlighting a shared concern about faith and recognition of God''s work.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 13, 41, 51, 1, 26, 27, 'work which ye shall in no wise believe', 'Mystery of Belief and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of a hidden work of God that is revealed to those who believe. Acts 13:41 warns of disbelief in God''s work, while Colossians 1:26-27 speaks of a mystery now made manifest to the saints.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
